"https://oldschoolessentials.necroticgnome.com/srd/index.php/Potion_of_Invisibility\">Invisibility</a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:2em;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:4em;text-align:center\"><p>73–76</p></td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:8em\"><a title=\"Potion of Invulnerability\" href=\"https://oldschoolessentials.necroticgnome.com/srd/index.php/Potion_of_Invulnerability\">Invulnerability</a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:2em;text-align:center\"><p>7</p></td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:4em;text-align:center\"><p>77–80</p></td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:8em\"><a title=\"Potion of Levitation\" href=\"https://oldschoolessentials.necroticgnome.com/srd/index.php/Potion_of_Levitation\">Levitation</a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:2em;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:4em;text-align:center\"><p>81–84</p></td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:8em\"><a title=\"Potion of Longevity\" href=\"https://oldschoolessentials.necroticgnome.com/srd/index.php/Potion_of_Longevity\">Longevity</a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:2em;text-align:center\"><p>8</p></td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:4em;text-align:center\"><p>85–86</p></td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:8em\"><a title=\"Potion of Poison\" href=\"https://oldschoolessentials.necroticgnome.com/srd/index.php/Potion_of_Poison\">Poison</a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:2em;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:4em;text-align:center\"><p>87–89</p></td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:8em\"><a title=\"Potion of Polymorph Self\" href=\"https://oldschoolessentials.necroticgnome.com/srd/index.php/Potion_of_Polymorph_Self\">Polymorph Self</a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:2em;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:4em;text-align:center\"><p>90–97</p></td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:8em\"><a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Speed\" href=\"https://oldschoolessentials.necroticgnome.com/srd/index.php/Speed\">Potion of Speed</a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:2em;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:4em;text-align:center\"><p>98–00</p></td><td style=\"border:none;padding:8px;width:8em\"><a title=\"Potion of Treasure Finding\" href=\"https://oldschoolessentials.necroticgnome.com/srd/index.php/Potion_of_Treasure_Finding\">Treasure Finding</a></td></tr></tbody></table><p><br /><strong>B:</strong> Basic characters (levels 1–3) <strong>X:</strong> Expert characters (level 4+)</p><p><strong>Usage:</strong> All characters (unless noted).</p><p><strong>Identifying:</strong> A potion may be identified by sipping a small amount. It is difficult to identify potions purely by smell or taste, as even potions with the same effect are not alike.</p><p><strong>Drinking:</strong> Drinking a full dose of a potion takes one round, and brings on the magical effect for 1d6+6 turns. The referee should roll for and track this duration, and not tell the player how long the potion will last for.</p><h2><span id=\"Mixing_Potions\" class=\"mw-headline\">Mixing Potions</span></h2><p>Drinking a potion while already under the effects of another potion is dangerous:</p><ul><li><strong>Sickness:</strong> The character is completely disabled for 3 turns, due to sickness.</li><li><strong>Cancellation:</strong> The effects of both potions are cancelled.</li></ul><p>This rule does not apply to potions with instantaneous or permanent duration. </p></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":800000,"name":"Rings","type":"text","_id":"CE6V0j1Gmc1eLxCA","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<